The paper discusses privacy concerns related to biometric identification cards, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of biometrics also involves image processing and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the need for transparency and user-centered design, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cryptography to protect privacy, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and secure information systems (cs.SI).
